videos.description: On two straight Kansas possessions, Devonte Graham lobs it up to Udoka Azubuike for a pair of dunks.
videos.headline: Graham finds Azubuike for back-to-back alley-oops

videos.description: Mitchell Solomon punishes the rim with a two-handed jam plus a foul.
videos.headline: Solomon fakes way to big dunk

videos.description: Kendall Smith scores just before halftime to give Oklahoma State a 16-point lead over Kansas.
videos.headline: Smith hits shot in final seconds of first half

videos.description: Jeffrey Carroll gets behind the defense and throws down a two-handed jam for Oklahoma State.
videos.headline: Carroll rattles rim with powerful jam

videos.description: Kendall Smith's nice pass allows Tavarius Shine to score on the fast break.
videos.headline: Shine scores layup in transition

videos.description: Kansas head coach Bill Self is frustrated after his team is called for an offensive foul leading to a technical foul.
videos.headline: Self picks up tech after offensive foul

videos.description: Oklahoma State's Mitchell Solomon talks about his big game and picking up a huge win over 6th ranked Kansas on senior day.
videos.headline: Solomon: 'So special' to get win in last home game
